## Test Anti-Pattern Audit — Severity-Ranked Findings

This test suite is a textbook case of **"coverage without verification"**. Every production method is exercised (→ 95% line coverage) but almost nothing is actually asserted. Here's the ranked list:

---

### 🔴 Critical — Tests That Prove Nothing

| # | Test | Anti-Pattern | Production Bug Risk |
|---|------|-------------|---------------------|
| 1 | `AddProduct_Works` (L17-21) | **No assertion at all.** Only calls the method. | `Save` could silently corrupt/discard data — test would still pass. |
| 2 | `UpdatePrice_Works` (L31-35) | **No assertion.** Calls `UpdatePrice` but never checks the price changed. | Price logic `p.Price * (1 - fraction)` vs `newPrice` — a regression here is invisible. |
| 3 | `RemoveProduct_Works` (L37-42) | **No assertion.** Never verifies the product is actually gone. | `Delete` could be a no-op and the test passes. |
| 4 | `GetProductCount_Works` (L63-66) | **No assertion + no setup data.** Always returns 0. | Count logic could return -1 or throw — still green. |
| 5 | `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L68-74) | **No assertion.** The most complex method in the class is completely unverified. | Off-by-one in `(1 - fraction)` (e.g., passing 10 instead of 0.10) would ship. |
| 6 | `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L84-88) | **No assertion.** Never checks products were actually imported. | Parsing bugs (wrong column order, culture-specific decimal parsing) invisible. |

---

### 🟠 High — Weak Assertions (Assert-IsNotNull-Only)

| # | Test | Problem | Fix |
|---|------|---------|-----|
| 7 | `GetProduct_Works` (L25-29) | `Assert.IsNotNull` only — never checks SKU, Name, or Price match. | A `FindBySku` returning a wrong/default product still passes. |
| 8 | `SearchProducts_Works` (L45-52) | `Assert.IsNotNull` on the list — never checks count or content. | Search returning *all* products or an empty list still passes. |
| 9 | `GetAllProducts_Works` (L55-60) | `Assert.IsNotNull` — never checks `Count == 1`. | Could return empty list forever. |
| 10 | `ExportToCsv_Works` (L76-82) | `Assert.IsNotNull` on string — never validates format. | CSV could be malformed (`;;` instead of `,`) — still green. |

---

### 🟡 Medium — Structural Issues

| # | Issue | Details |
|---|-------|---------|
| 11 | **No negative/edge-case tests** | `UpdatePrice` on missing SKU should throw `KeyNotFoundException` — untested. |
| 12 | **No boundary testing** | `ApplyBulkDiscount(1.0m)` (100% off), `ApplyBulkDiscount(0m)` — untested. |
